dismissalText.commentary: Hamilton Masakadza run out (Khaled Mashud/sub [Mohammad Ashraful]) 2 (8b 0x4 0x6 18m) SR: 25

dismissalComment.html: soft run out - classic mix-up and Zimbabwe pay the price with Masakadza sacrificing himself. Taylor middled the ball with a good shot which took the opposing stumps and the richochet was quickly gathered and returned to the keeper who waited and took the stumps. Taylor set off and Masakadza was stranded in no-man's land, and he crossed with the scampering Taylor to let that batsman stay in.

commentTextItems.html: and that's it, game over. He goes back to one that he should be forward to, it careers past a flapping bat, taking out all three.

commentPostTextItems.html: Well done Bangladesh! That's their first Champions Trophy win ever and they regain bottom of the table bragging rites. Zimbabwe have folded once more, but at least one of their batsman made 50. Zimbabwe were poor in this tournament and, as soon as the pace came off the ball on this slow wicket, they were always going to struggle. Bangladesh's score was, looking back, probably better than par. And thanks for joining me on my debut - and the rest of the team - from all of us here, good night.

dismissalText.commentary: Brendan Taylor st Khaled Mashud b Shakib Al Hasan 52 (74b 7x4 0x6 97m) SR: 70.27

dismissalComment.html: looks dangerous this, Taylor's been dragged out of his crease, over-balanced and Mashud has whipped off the bails. They are going to the third umpire but Taylor has walked. That could be it...

dismissalText.commentary: Hamilton Masakadza run out (Khaled Mashud/sub [Mohammad Ashraful]) 2 (8b 0x4 0x6 18m) SR: 25

dismissalComment.html: soft run out - classic mix-up and Zimbabwe pay the price with Masakadza sacrificing himself. Taylor middled the ball with a good shot which took the opposing stumps and the richochet was quickly gathered and returned to the keeper who waited and took the stumps. Taylor set off and Masakadza was stranded in no-man's land, and he crossed with the scampering Taylor to let that batsman stay in.

dismissalText.commentary: Gregory Strydom b Mohammad Rafique 4 (22b 0x4 0x6 24m) SR: 18.18

dismissalComment.html: cleaned him right up with a quicker one that rocketed against the pads off the bat and straight into the sticks. This wicket was always on the cards with Strydom struggling against the spin.

headshotImage.caption: Syed Rasel player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Stuart Matsikenyeri run out (Shakib Al Hasan/sub [Syed Rasel]) 9 (18b 1x4 0x6 20m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: dear oh dear, Taylor has worked it to deep backward square, turned for a quick second but Matsikenyeri has not moved - poor Taylor looked up to see his partner unmoved at the other end. For the second time in the innings, Taylor sprints passed a partner, running him out.

dismissalText.commentary: Elton Chigumbura c & b Shakib Al Hasan 27 (53b 0x4 0x6 46m) SR: 50.94
